<task id="074" project="file-preview-dialog-with-auth-enhancements">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate AnalysisWorkspace PCF Auth + Reconcile SDAP.Access vs user_impersonation Scope</title>
    <phase>8</phase>
    <tags>auth, migration, pcf, scope-reconciliation</tags>
    <estimate>4-5 hours</estimate>
    <dependencies>060</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>F</parallel-group>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Replace AnalysisWorkspace PCF auth with @spaarke/auth and reconcile SDAP.Access vs user_impersonation scope — removing ~1,418 lines</goal>
    <context>
      AnalysisWorkspace PCF has the second-largest auth footprint: AuthService.ts (243 lines),
      MsalAuthProvider.ts (793 lines), msalConfig.ts (337 lines), and auth.ts types (45 lines)
      totaling ~1,418 lines. This is the most complex PCF migration because it uses a DIFFERENT
      OAuth scope name (SDAP.Access) compared to other controls (user_impersonation).

      CRITICAL INVESTIGATION REQUIRED: Before migrating, you must verify whether SDAP.Access and
      user_impersonation are the same Azure AD permission (just different names/aliases) or genuinely
      different permissions. If they are different, the @spaarke/auth default scope configuration
      may need to be extended to support both.

      The pilot migration (task 060) validated the general PCF migration pattern. This task adds
      the scope reconciliation complexity on top.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST investigate SDAP.Access vs user_impersonation scope BEFORE migrating
      - MUST verify these scopes resolve to the same Azure AD permission, or handle both
      - MUST follow the proven pilot pattern from task 060 for the auth migration itself
      - MUST update all service consumers
      - MUST remove all auth files after migration
      - MUST bump ControlManifest.Input.xml version
      - MUST document scope reconciliation findings for future reference
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/pcf/AnalysisWorkspace/control/services/AuthService.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/AnalysisWorkspace/control/services/auth/MsalAuthProvider.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/AnalysisWorkspace/control/services/auth/msalConfig.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/AnalysisWorkspace/control/services/auth/auth.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/oauth-scopes.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/pcf.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read current auth files: AuthService.ts (243 lines), MsalAuthProvider.ts (793 lines), msalConfig.ts (337 lines), auth.ts (45 lines)</step>
    <step>Identify the SDAP.Access scope usage in msalConfig.ts and compare with user_impersonation scope used elsewhere</step>
    <step>Investigate whether SDAP.Access and user_impersonation resolve to the same Azure AD app registration permission (check Azure AD app manifest or documentation)</step>
    <step>If same permission: proceed with standard @spaarke/auth migration using default scope</step>
    <step>If different permissions: configure @spaarke/auth to support the correct scope for this control</step>
    <step>Install @spaarke/auth as a dependency</step>
    <step>Replace AuthService and MsalAuthProvider with initAuth() using the reconciled scope configuration</step>
    <step>Update all service consumers to use authenticatedFetch()</step>
    <step>Remove all auth files: AuthService.ts, MsalAuthProvider.ts, msalConfig.ts, auth.ts, and auth/ directory</step>
    <step>Remove @azure/msal-browser from direct dependencies if no longer needed</step>
    <step>Document scope reconciliation findings in project notes</step>
    <step>Bump version in ControlManifest.Input.xml</step>
    <step>Build PCF control and verify no errors</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output>src/client/pcf/AnalysisWorkspace/package.json (updated with @spaarke/auth)</output>
    <output>src/client/pcf/AnalysisWorkspace/control/index.ts (updated init)</output>
    <output>src/client/pcf/AnalysisWorkspace/control/services/ (consumers updated, auth/ removed)</output>
    <output>src/client/pcf/AnalysisWorkspace/ControlManifest.Input.xml (version bumped)</output>
    <output>projects/file-preview-dialog-with-auth-enhancements/notes/scope-reconciliation.md (findings)</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>SDAP.Access vs user_impersonation scope reconciliation documented</criterion>
    <criterion>AuthService.ts (243 lines) deleted</criterion>
    <criterion>MsalAuthProvider.ts (793 lines) deleted</criterion>
    <criterion>msalConfig.ts (337 lines) deleted</criterion>
    <criterion>auth.ts (45 lines) deleted</criterion>
    <criterion>auth/ directory completely removed</criterion>
    <criterion>Correct scope configured in @spaarke/auth initAuth() call</criterion>
    <criterion>All consumers use authenticatedFetch()</criterion>
    <criterion>ControlManifest.Input.xml version bumped</criterion>
    <criterion>PCF build compiles without errors</criterion>
    <criterion>Net line removal: ~1,418 lines</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
